{
    if (obj is string str)
    {

    }
}
```
`str` is in the resulted code even though it isn't used. I think, in such cases codefix should remove unused variables. It is very unlikely that you will use this codefix while typing because such code style is kinda ancient nowadays and most likely you will use it to refactor an old code bases where it is already known if the variable is later used or not

